    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <head>No. 1082.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 17,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 96.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 71 of the 30th
                        ultimo, in which the Ottoman Government requests you to instruct the consul
                        of the United States at Odessa not to interpose objection to the return to
                        Turkey of H. A. Proios, whose extradition is demanded from Russia.</p>
                <p>Mr. Thomas E. Heenan, the consul, has been called upon for full information
                        in regard to the case.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
